# Learning with AI  
## I2C Communication with Sensors

**Project:** Mold Growth Risk Predictor  
**Name:** Idalia Martin  

---

## Why I2C is Important

- Used to connect sensors in IoT systems  
- Reduces wiring complexity  
- Enables reliable communication between ESP32 and AHT10 sensor  

Without I2C, the system cannot collect environmental data

---

## What I Learned

- How ESP32 communicates with AHT10 using SDA and SCL  
- How to wire the sensor correctly (3.3V, GND, SDA, SCL)  
- How to scan for I2C devices (address 0x38)  
- How to read temperature and humidity data  

---

## How I Applied It

- Connected AHT10 sensor to ESP32  
- Used I2C scanner to detect the device  
- Retrieved real-time temperature and humidity readings  
- Debugged wiring and connection issues  

---

## Challenges & Solutions

- Sensor not detected → fixed wiring  
- Wrong pin mapping → learned GPIO vs labeled pins  
- Library errors → installed correct Adafruit library  

---

## How AI Helped Me

- Explained I2C communication in simple terms  
- Helped debug connection issues  
- Interpreted error messages  
- Guided correct wiring and setup  

---

## Reflection

- I started with no experience in hardware communication  
- Learned how sensors communicate with microcontrollers  
- Successfully built a working sensor system  
